				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "###What are we trying to model?\n\nEvery business system talks about things.\n\nPeople.\nCompanies.\nGovernment agencies.\nDepartments.\nProjects.\n\nMartin Fowler calls all of these Parties.\n\nThe only thing we know today is that there are different kinds of parties.\n\nNothing else.\n\nNotice what we are not introducing:\n\naddresses\nnames\nidentifiers\ntypes\nobservations\naccountabilities\n\nThose all represent assumptions we have not yet earned.\n\nOur first model is almost embarrassingly small.A person exists, an organization exists. Both are parties."
			},
